1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Scene 1: Japan vs. Brazil Match – Our Thoughts

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,590
Did you watch the soccer match yesterday?

3
00:00:07,614 --> 00:00:11,391
Yeah, I did.

4
00:00:11,414 --> 00:00:15,514
The Japan vs. Brazil game, right?

5
00:00:15,537 --> 00:00:18,171
That’s the one.

6
00:00:18,194 --> 00:00:23,627
Japan lost 1-2.

7
00:00:23,650 --> 00:00:27,750
Such a shame, really.

8
00:00:27,773 --> 00:00:32,906
But they put on a great fight till the end.

9
00:00:32,929 --> 00:00:35,398
Absolutely.

10
00:00:35,422 --> 00:00:40,960
Japan’s first-half goal was just beautiful.

11
00:00:40,984 --> 00:00:44,569
Got me so hyped!

12
00:00:44,592 --> 00:00:49,325
Their defense was solid too.

13
00:00:49,348 --> 00:00:51,946
No doubt.

14
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:58,368
They stopped Brazil’s attacks over and over.

15
00:00:58,391 --> 00:01:05,172
Even from the start, Brazil really turned it up in the second half.

16
00:01:05,196 --> 00:01:07,465
Yeah, they did.

17
00:01:07,488 --> 00:01:14,257
Brazil’s passing in the second half was lightning fast.

18
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:19,783
That final goal was an absolute rocket.

19
00:01:19,807 --> 00:01:25,274
No surprise—they *are* the world’s top-ranked team.

20
00:01:25,297 --> 00:01:29,217
They were a tough wall to break.

21
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:36,473
Frustrating, but those tears from Japan’s players got to me.

22
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:42,432
I couldn’t stop clapping for them on TV.

23
00:01:42,456 --> 00:01:50,245
We made it to the Round of 16—no need to hang our heads.

24
00:01:50,268 --> 00:01:52,706
Absolutely.

25
00:01:52,730 --> 00:01:59,209
They proved they can battle with the best.

26
00:01:59,232 --> 00:02:05,782
I’m already excited for the next World Cup in four years.

27
00:02:05,805 --> 00:02:07,987
Yeah, they did.

28
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:14,044
We’ll see an even stronger Japan next time.

29
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:20,567
Until then, let’s keep cheering together.

30
00:02:20,590 --> 00:02:23,023
No doubt.

31
00:02:23,046 --> 00:02:29,154
Today, let’s eat something delicious and lift our spirits!

32
00:02:29,178 --> 00:02:31,711
Sounds good!

33
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:36,034
How about we grab some yakiniku?

34
00:02:36,057 --> 00:02:39,057
Scene 2: World Cup Final – Who’s Making It?

35
00:02:39,057 --> 00:02:45,235
The World Cup is really heating up now, isn’t it?

36
00:02:45,259 --> 00:02:52,767
Yeah, the teams left are all powerhouses.

37
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:59,724
So, who’s your pick for the final matchup this year?

38
00:02:59,747 --> 00:03:06,546
I think it’ll be Brazil vs. France.

39
00:03:06,569 --> 00:03:10,836
A classic showdown.

40
00:03:10,859 --> 00:03:14,759
Why those two?

41
00:03:14,782 --> 00:03:21,661
Brazil’s on fire in this tournament.

42
00:03:21,685 --> 00:03:25,399
True that.

43
00:03:25,422 --> 00:03:31,127
Neymar’s attack game is insane.

44
00:03:31,151 --> 00:03:36,984
France’s defense is rock solid, though.

45
00:03:37,007 --> 00:03:41,641
They’ve got that reigning-champion energy.

46
00:03:41,664 --> 00:03:45,565
Mbappé’s speed is unreal.

47
00:03:45,588 --> 00:03:52,294
Exactly. That’s why they’ll make the final.

48
00:03:52,318 --> 00:03:56,757
Who do you think will win it all?

49
00:03:56,780 --> 00:03:59,962
Come on, take a real guess!

50
00:03:59,985 --> 00:04:06,092
I’m betting on Brazil to take the title.

51
00:04:06,115 --> 00:04:11,415
Is it because of their individual skill?

52
00:04:11,438 --> 00:04:14,105
Yeah, they did.

53
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:21,761
South America’s free-flowing style will break Europe’s structure.

54
00:04:21,784 --> 00:04:26,818
Now *that’s* an interesting take.

55
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:30,974
I think it's going to be France.

56
00:04:30,997 --> 00:04:34,706
France winning back-to-back?

57
00:04:34,729 --> 00:04:37,863
What's the reason?

58
00:04:37,886 --> 00:04:43,753
No matter who plays, their depth of talent is incredible.

59
00:04:43,776 --> 00:04:47,850
They have so many tactical options.

60
00:04:47,873 --> 00:04:54,552
True. Even if key players get injured, the team doesn’t lose its strength.

61
00:04:54,575 --> 00:05:00,475
The final is going to be an all-time classic.

62
00:05:00,498 --> 00:05:04,965
Either team could win—it’s that close.

63
00:05:04,988 --> 00:05:08,555
I’m already getting excited!

64
00:05:08,578 --> 00:05:11,578
Scene 3: The Thrill of Watching Sumo Live

65
00:05:11,578 --> 00:05:18,286
How about going to watch sumo this weekend?

66
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:21,076
Sumo?

67
00:05:21,099 --> 00:05:26,533
I’ve never seen it live before.

68
00:05:26,556 --> 00:05:29,456
You should definitely go!

69
00:05:29,479 --> 00:05:33,712
The venue is Ryogoku Kokugikan.

70
00:05:33,735 --> 00:05:39,888
I’ve seen it on TV, but is it really more intense in person?

71
00:05:39,911 --> 00:05:44,544
Oh, it’s completely different.

72
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:49,667
The wrestlers are *massive* in real life.

73
00:05:49,690 --> 00:05:54,824
Can you hear the sound of their bodies colliding from the seats?

74
00:05:54,847 --> 00:06:02,381
Yes! The *thud* echoes through the whole arena—it’s incredible.

75
00:06:02,404 --> 00:06:06,104
That sounds amazing!

76
00:06:06,127 --> 00:06:10,198
Are tickets still available?

77
00:06:10,222 --> 00:06:15,922
Second-floor reserved seats are still open.

78
00:06:15,945 --> 00:06:18,703
Great!

79
00:06:18,726 --> 00:06:24,400
Can we eat bento inside the arena?

80
00:06:24,424 --> 00:06:28,158
Yes, that’s fine.

81
00:06:28,181 --> 00:06:33,314
The yakitori is a must-try—it’s delicious!

82
00:06:33,337 --> 00:06:37,729
Yakitori at a sumo venue?

83
00:06:37,752 --> 00:06:40,486
That’s unexpected!

84
00:06:40,509 --> 00:06:47,143
It’s a special souvenir—grilled fresh in the basement of the arena.

85
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:50,232
And it’s still tasty even when it cools down.

86
00:06:50,255 --> 00:06:54,224
I *have* to try that!

87
00:06:54,248 --> 00:06:57,827
Do they serve chanko nabe too?

88
00:06:57,850 --> 00:07:06,550
Yes! You can get a real chanko nabe in the main hall for just 500 yen.

89
00:07:06,573 --> 00:07:09,440
That’s a steal!

90
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:15,799
You get to enjoy both traditional culture and great food.

91
00:07:15,822 --> 00:07:21,368
They also sell lots of merchandise for popular wrestlers.

92
00:07:21,392 --> 00:07:25,500
Who’s the strongest right now?

93
00:07:25,523 --> 00:07:28,259
Tell me!

94
00:07:28,282 --> 00:07:32,453
Yokozuna Terunofuji.

95
00:07:32,477 --> 00:07:36,710
He’s fought through injuries and never gives up.

96
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:40,284
He’s the kind of wrestler you can’t help but root for.

97
00:07:40,308 --> 00:07:44,503
I can’t wait for the weekend!

98
00:07:44,526 --> 00:07:47,526
Scene 4: The Climbing Big Three’s Fierce Rivalry

99
00:07:47,526 --> 00:07:59,273
You can’t miss the men’s sport climbing competitions lately—young athletes are dominating the world stage!

100
00:07:59,297 --> 00:08:06,997
Absolutely, especially Japan’s Haruto Anraku—he’s incredible.

101
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:14,886
He’s been winning major adult competitions since he was still in high school!

102
00:08:14,909 --> 00:08:21,014
The battles between him and his rivals are next-level.

103
00:08:21,038 --> 00:08:27,115
France’s Mejdi Schalck is called a genius, right?

104
00:08:27,138 --> 00:08:38,297
Mejdi excels in bouldering—his movements are so dynamic! And we can’t forget Korea’s Dohyun Lee either.

105
00:08:38,321 --> 00:08:45,491
Athlete I makes light work of even the toughest walls with incredible power.

106
00:08:45,515 --> 00:08:52,815
Watching these three rivals go head-to-head is absolutely electrifying.

107
00:08:52,837 --> 00:09:00,271
At last month’s World Cup, the standings were unpredictable until the very end.

108
00:09:00,294 --> 00:09:03,127
That’s right.

109
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:08,730
When Anraku pulled off that comeback, I got chills.

110
00:09:08,754 --> 00:09:16,866
Off the wall, they’re apparently really close friends.

111
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:20,756
After the match, they hugged each other with big smiles.

112
00:09:20,779 --> 00:09:26,368
They push each other to be better—what an amazing dynamic.

113
00:09:26,392 --> 00:09:33,727
I can’t wait to see these three battle it out for the podium at the next international competition.

114
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:39,283
It’s an era where any of them could win—it’s anyone’s game.

115
00:09:39,306 --> 00:09:43,901
Climbing’s popularity is about to skyrocket.

116
00:09:43,925 --> 00:09:49,558
Let’s cheer them on from home!

117
00:09:49,581 --> 00:09:55,281
Yeah, I’ll make sure to check the live stream time.

118
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:58,304
Scene 5: Mori Aya’s Magical Lead Climbing

119
00:09:58,304 --> 00:10:03,661
Women’s sport climbing is just as thrilling.

120
00:10:03,685 --> 00:10:08,718
Japan has a true lead-climbing prodigy.

121
00:10:08,741 --> 00:10:10,522
Yeah, they did.

122
00:10:10,545 --> 00:10:16,660
Mori Aya’s climbs are like magic.

123
00:10:16,684 --> 00:10:22,317
Her lead performances always leave me in awe.

124
00:10:22,340 --> 00:10:28,973
There are sections where even top international climbers fall.

125
00:10:28,996 --> 00:10:30,952
Absolutely.

126
00:10:30,976 --> 00:10:36,676
But Mori glides right through them effortlessly.

127
00:10:36,699 --> 00:10:43,166
It’s like she defies gravity, clinging to the wall.

128
00:10:43,189 --> 00:10:49,826
Her core strength and endurance are on another level.

129
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:56,949
Mori’s a bit shorter than the other climbers, isn’t she?

130
00:10:56,972 --> 00:10:59,283
Yeah, they did.

131
00:10:59,306 --> 00:11:05,339
She compensates for her reach with razor-sharp technique.

132
00:11:05,362 --> 00:11:13,114
All that relentless training must be behind her flawless movements.

133
00:11:13,138 --> 00:11:20,696
The contrast between her intense focus during competition and her warm smile afterward is so endearing.

134
00:11:20,719 --> 00:11:26,953
She’s usually a quiet, unassuming college student.

135
00:11:26,976 --> 00:11:33,876
But once she steps in front of that wall, she transforms into the world’s best climber.

136
00:11:33,899 --> 00:11:39,665
Watching her climb makes me want to get active too.

137
00:11:39,688 --> 00:11:44,122
There’s a bouldering gym nearby, you know.

138
00:11:44,145 --> 00:11:46,721
Want to check it out?

139
00:11:46,744 --> 00:11:50,141
Is it beginner-friendly?

140
00:11:50,165 --> 00:11:53,332
I’m a little nervous.

141
00:11:53,355 --> 00:11:59,192
They’ll start you on easy routes, and the staff are super helpful.

142
00:11:59,215 --> 00:12:04,749
Let’s book a trial session for this weekend!

143
00:12:04,772 --> 00:12:09,549
Make sure to wear something comfy.

144
00:12:09,572 --> 00:12:12,572
Scene 6: Japanese MLB Players' Remarkable Performances

145
00:12:12,572 --> 00:12:18,839
MLB news is buzzing every day.

146
00:12:18,862 --> 00:12:25,429
Absolutely. Japanese players in the majors are on fire.

147
00:12:25,452 --> 00:12:30,806
This morning, one of them crushed a massive home run.

148
00:12:30,829 --> 00:12:37,026
The ball flew so far, it was unbelievable.

149
00:12:37,049 --> 00:12:44,218
He’s like a real-life manga protagonist.

150
00:12:44,242 --> 00:12:51,611
And when he pitches, he’s racking up strikeouts with 100 mph fastballs.

151
00:12:51,634 --> 00:12:58,268
Even the baseball gods must be impressed.

152
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:05,233
American fans are going wild for him in the stadiums.

153
00:13:05,256 --> 00:13:11,589
Merchandise sales are at an all-time high for the team.

154
00:13:11,612 --> 00:13:18,879
Local kids are all wearing his jersey.

155
00:13:18,902 --> 00:13:26,856
He’s not just a phenomenal player—his sportsmanship, like picking up trash, is earning praise too.

156
00:13:26,879 --> 00:13:33,712
With his talent and character, it’s no wonder he’s loved worldwide.

157
00:13:33,735 --> 00:13:41,035
Just seeing his highlights in the morning gives me energy for the whole day.

158
00:13:41,058 --> 00:13:45,030
A true source of pride for Japan.

159
00:13:45,054 --> 00:13:49,387
The ultimate entertainment.

160
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:56,584
I’d love to experience a game live in the U.S. at least once in my life.

161
00:13:56,608 --> 00:14:00,941
That’s a stadium in Los Angeles.

162
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:04,798
I’d love to go too.

163
00:14:04,821 --> 00:14:10,621
Maybe we should look into travel agency tours?

164
00:14:10,644 --> 00:14:16,311
It might be pricey, but it’s absolutely worth seeing.

165
00:14:16,334 --> 00:14:19,367
No doubt.

166
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:24,733
I’ll work hard and save up for it.

167
00:14:24,757 --> 00:14:31,532
I’ll start saving little by little too.

168
00:14:31,555 --> 00:14:34,555
Scene 7: The Charm of Japanese Professional Baseball

169
00:14:34,555 --> 00:14:40,313
Have you ever been to a Japanese professional baseball game?

170
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:45,084
Yes, I’ve been several times.

171
00:14:45,108 --> 00:14:49,541
I love the atmosphere at the stadium.

172
00:14:49,564 --> 00:14:56,731
Japan’s cheering culture is totally different from baseball abroad, right?

173
00:14:56,754 --> 00:15:04,120
Definitely. I think any first-time visitor from overseas would be surprised.

174
00:15:04,143 --> 00:15:10,612
The cheer squad in the right-field stands plays trumpets, right?

175
00:15:10,636 --> 00:15:17,809
Yeah, and the whole crowd sings along at the top of their lungs.

176
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:24,375
It’s so fun how each player has their own unique cheer song.

177
00:15:24,399 --> 00:15:30,865
It’s so cool when your song plays as you step up to bat.

178
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:37,522
There’s a special event before the seventh-inning stretch, too.

179
00:15:37,545 --> 00:15:44,487
They release colorful jet balloons along with the team’s song.

180
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,343
That’s the one.

181
00:15:47,366 --> 00:15:52,835
The sight of balloons filling the sky is breathtaking.

182
00:15:52,858 --> 00:16:00,001
It makes the whole stadium feel like a festival.

183
00:16:00,025 --> 00:16:07,142
The stadium food is another highlight, not just the game.

184
00:16:07,165 --> 00:16:13,485
There are so many bento boxes and sweets created by the players themselves.

185
00:16:13,508 --> 00:16:20,541
With dome stadiums, you don’t have to worry about rain cancellations.

186
00:16:20,564 --> 00:16:26,464
And nothing beats an ice-cold beer from the vendors walking around.

187
00:16:26,487 --> 00:16:32,754
How about we invite a bunch of friends and go together next time?

188
00:16:32,777 --> 00:16:36,844
The more, the merrier!

189
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:40,900
Let’s check the schedule for next month’s games.

190
00:16:40,923 --> 00:16:47,823
A Friday night game would work—we could go after work.

191
00:16:47,846 --> 00:16:50,113
Sounds good!

192
00:16:50,136 --> 00:16:54,727
Let’s make it a premium Friday night out!

193
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:57,750
Scene 8: Evolution of Japan's National Volleyball Team Tactics

194
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:05,736
Japan’s men’s national volleyball team has gotten so strong lately.

195
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:12,526
They’ve been defeating powerhouse teams one after another in world tournaments.

196
00:17:12,549 --> 00:17:19,616
Compared to the old days, their tactics have evolved so much.

197
00:17:19,639 --> 00:17:27,276
Absolutely. Their offensive speed is unbelievably fast.

198
00:17:27,299 --> 00:17:34,204
The setters are so skilled at placing the ball, they fool the opposing blockers.

199
00:17:34,228 --> 00:17:40,505
And their back-row attacks are so powerful.

200
00:17:40,528 --> 00:17:47,086
The liberos’ receiving skills are world-class too.

201
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:54,468
No matter how hard the spike, they keep it off the floor—it’s incredible.

202
00:17:54,492 --> 00:18:00,034
The players are also good-looking, which adds to their popularity.

203
00:18:00,058 --> 00:18:06,411
The stands are packed with fans at every match.

204
00:18:06,434 --> 00:18:13,829
But I think their popularity comes from their high level of skill.

205
00:18:13,852 --> 00:18:17,119
I agree.

206
00:18:17,142 --> 00:18:22,889
Every player fights tooth and nail to keep the ball in play for the team.

207
00:18:22,912 --> 00:18:30,079
Volleyball is a sport where you can’t hold the ball, after all.

208
00:18:30,102 --> 00:18:37,135
Exactly. That’s why trust in your teammates is the most important thing.

209
00:18:37,158 --> 00:18:45,258
Watching them play, I can’t help but get fired up and cheer even harder.

210
00:18:45,281 --> 00:18:52,448
I really think they have a great shot at winning a medal in the next Olympics.

211
00:18:52,471 --> 00:18:58,337
I want to witness a moment that changes history with my own eyes.

212
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:04,352
There’s a live game broadcast on TV tonight.

213
00:19:04,376 --> 00:19:11,126
I’ve got to rush home and get ready in front of the TV.

214
00:19:11,149 --> 00:19:16,249
I’ll grab some snacks and cheer along with you!

215
00:19:16,272 --> 00:19:19,272
Scene 9: The Thrill of Watching a B.League Game

216
00:19:19,272 --> 00:19:26,739
I watched my first B.League game last weekend.

217
00:19:26,762 --> 00:19:30,836
Japan’s pro basketball league, right?

218
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:33,769
How was it?

219
00:19:33,792 --> 00:19:40,825
The atmosphere inside the arena felt like a nightclub.

220
00:19:40,848 --> 00:19:46,956
I’ve heard there’s loud music and flashy lighting.

221
00:19:46,979 --> 00:19:49,513
Yeah, they did.

222
00:19:49,536 --> 00:19:55,769
Before the game even started, the DJ was hyping up the crowd.

223
00:19:55,792 --> 00:20:02,059
It’s a space where even people who don’t know basketball can have fun.

224
00:20:02,082 --> 00:20:10,415
Yeah, and once the game began, I was blown away by the speed.

225
00:20:10,438 --> 00:20:16,371
The court’s so small, you’re really close to the players.

226
00:20:16,394 --> 00:20:23,828
When I saw a dunk right in front of me, I let out a huge cheer.

227
00:20:23,851 --> 00:20:28,717
It was so intense, it felt like the hoop was about to break!

228
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:30,974
Yeah, they did.

229
00:20:30,997 --> 00:20:37,032
And you never knew how the game would turn out until the very end.

230
00:20:37,055 --> 00:20:43,522
Last-second comebacks are what make basketball so thrilling.

231
00:20:43,545 --> 00:20:47,020
Exactly!

232
00:20:47,044 --> 00:20:52,917
A three-pointer went in with just three seconds left.

233
00:20:52,940 --> 00:20:56,173
That was an epic win!

234
00:20:56,196 --> 00:21:00,629
You could feel the excitement from the crowd.

235
00:21:00,652 --> 00:21:07,848
The cheers were so loud, the whole arena shook—I got chills!

236
00:21:07,871 --> 00:21:12,052
How much were the tickets?

237
00:21:12,076 --> 00:21:18,624
For regular seats, you can get one for around 3,000 yen per adult.

238
00:21:18,647 --> 00:21:24,881
For that price and that level of entertainment? It’s an amazing deal.

239
00:21:24,904 --> 00:21:29,804
Want to go watch a game together next time?

240
00:21:29,827 --> 00:21:32,860
You’ll definitely get hooked.

241
00:21:32,883 --> 00:21:36,716
Please take me with you!

242
00:21:36,739 --> 00:21:40,337
I want to buy some team merch too.

243
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:46,060
Let’s wear team-colored T-shirts and make some noise!

244
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:49,083
Scene 10: The Intense Table Tennis Showdown

245
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:55,617
I watched the finals of an international table tennis tournament on TV.

246
00:21:55,640 --> 00:22:00,806
It was an intense battle between Japan and China.

247
00:22:00,829 --> 00:22:03,529
Did you see it?

248
00:22:03,552 --> 00:22:05,868
Yeah, they did.

249
00:22:05,892 --> 00:22:12,287
The rallies were so fast, I couldn’t even blink!

250
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:18,943
They’re trading shots in a split-second world.

251
00:22:18,966 --> 00:22:25,600
Their reflexes and dynamic vision are superhuman.

252
00:22:25,623 --> 00:22:34,689
China, the undisputed champions, are an incredibly tough wall to break.

253
00:22:34,712 --> 00:22:41,046
They have so many spin variations and never make mistakes.

254
00:22:41,069 --> 00:22:49,010
But the young Japanese players never gave up until the end.

255
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:57,107
Yeah, when they took a set from the Chinese champ, I screamed!

256
00:22:57,130 --> 00:23:04,163
Their loud battle cries when they scored were so hype.

257
00:23:04,186 --> 00:23:07,920
Absolutely.

258
00:23:07,943 --> 00:23:13,380
You could feel their fighting spirit through the screen.

259
00:23:13,403 --> 00:23:20,270
It used to be called a boring sport, but not anymore.

260
00:23:20,293 --> 00:23:27,632
Now it’s one of Japan’s most popular and exciting sports.

261
00:23:27,655 --> 00:23:33,968
The number of kids playing is growing fast, I’ve heard.

262
00:23:33,991 --> 00:23:40,858
It’s exciting to think future medalists are being raised right now.

263
00:23:40,881 --> 00:23:48,351
Watching the match made me want to play some hot springs table tennis!

264
00:23:48,374 --> 00:23:54,407
We'll need to start with how to hold the racket, won't we?

265
00:23:54,430 --> 00:24:01,428
At a hot spring ping pong table, even beginners can have fun with a smile!

266
00:24:01,451 --> 00:24:07,685
Let's plan a hot spring getaway for some relaxation soon!

267
00:24:07,708 --> 00:24:14,141
I'll look up inns with ping pong tables online right away!